==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Methol
<hw>Meth"ol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ wine +
<ets>-ol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An earlier technical name
of methyl alcohol or wood spirit, now called
<altname>methanol</altname>; also, by extension, the class name of any
of the series of alcohols of the methane series of which
<xex>methol</xex> proper is the type. See <cref>Methyl alcohol</cref>,
under <er>Methyl</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

